281
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:05,560
This jar of Xifeng wine

282
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,220
was buried more than ten years ago

283
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,520
by Constable Qin and me.

284
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,640
At that time, we agreed that

285
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:14,160
if we solved a major case,

286
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,560
we would dig it up

287
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,820
and drink to our hearts' content.

288
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,320
Today, we solved a major case,

289
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:21,840
so I brought it out.

290
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,080
Then we must have a good drink.

291
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:26,200
You kid, you really can solve any case.

292
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:29,160
There is no unsolvable case in this world,

293
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,440
only unseen clues and truths.

294
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,640
Time to eat.

295
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:36,240
Smells so good.

296
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,250
These dishes are great.

297
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:43,640
I have to say,

298
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,240
you really look

299
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,660
a bit like Constable Qin around the eyes.

300
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:48,880
But don't be proud,

301
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:50,880
you are still far behind him.

302
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,840
Constable Qin solved countless cases in his life.

303
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,660
We called him a divine detective.

304
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,680
To me, Constable Qin

305
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,570
was both a teacher and a friend.

306
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,400
Today,

307
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:08,080
by solving major cases one after another,

308
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:11,920
we can comfort his soul in heaven.

309
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,480
Constable Qin, I toast to you first.

310
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,040
I toast to Constable Qin too.

311
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,120
Constable Qin wasn't a heavy drinker,

312
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,050
these two bowls are enough for him.

313
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:30,760
It's obvious you're reluctant to part with this wine.

314
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:32,840
This wine is indeed precious.

315
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,530
I've saved it for ten years.

316
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,280
Today we solved a major case,

317
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,200
let's have a good drink together.

318
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,720
Here, son.

319
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:41,600
Thank you, Dad. Miss.

320
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,440
Thank you.

321
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,120
Cheers.

322
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:53,400
Constable Qin,

323
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:55,240
how did he die?

324
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,600
That day,

325
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,260
the Qin family suddenly caught fire,

326
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:06,160
and five people in his family were burned to death.

327
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,000
His father Qin Boyan,

328
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,760
his wife Su Yuerong,

329
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:12,160
his son Qin Nian,

330
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:15,000
and their daughter Qin Wan'er.

331
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,600
What caused the fire?

332
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,040
Was it investigated?

333
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:20,440
Yes, it was.

334
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:22,800
It was investigated very carefully.

335
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,880
It was just an ordinary accidental fire,

336
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,080
and the case was closed in a few days.

337
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,720
But when I was learning to be a coroner,

338
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,360
my teacher's teacher

339
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,600
was old Mr. Qin Boyan.

340
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:40,240
I guess I received the old master's true teachings.

341
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,000
He had a book back then

342
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,240
called Records of Corpse Examination.

343
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:47,360
It recorded a lot of things about autopsies,

344
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:50,360
a lot of real content and key points.

345
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,600
Too many.

346
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,400
It's just a pity it was lost.

347
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,090
I can never see it again.

348
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,360
Do you really want to read it?

349
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:02,080
I have it here.

350
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,640
Stop joking.

351
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,760
It's right there.

352
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,920
Come, let's drink.

353
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,000
Where is it?

354
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,040
Where is it?

355
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:17,280
Over here.

356
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,660
The one in the middle of the first row.

357
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,800
You really have it!

358
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,120
Would I lie to you?

359
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,240
Why do you have it?

360
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:36,240
I used to hang around the ghost market in my early years.

361
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,770
They had everything there.

362
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,040
So whenever I saw something I liked,

363
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:42,140
I would buy a couple of copies to read.

364
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:43,960
In that case,

365
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:46,040
you must have more strange tales and weird records.

366
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,480
Can I have a look too?

367
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:48,680
I actually have quite a few.

368
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:49,400
Go ahead.

369
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:50,680
All right.

370
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,980
I won't be polite then.

371
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,040
Come on, let's drink.

372
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:55,240
Let me have a look too.

373
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,800
Let's see what's good here.

374
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,240
'Family Rules of the Leng Family'.

375
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:02,200
What is this?

376
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:03,640
What is this?

377
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,920
'Legend of the Strange Swordsmen'.

378
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,080
I've read this one.

379
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,040
'Collection of Beishan Tower'.

380
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,840
I've read this too.

381
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,640
You definitely wouldn't put the good stuff out in the open.

382
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:17,720
Let me see.

383
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:19,940
What good stuff is hidden in here?

384
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:20,920
Miss.

385
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:21,560
Hmm?

386
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,530
Come take a look.

387
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,760
Here is a couplet with elegant handwriting.

388
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:25,600
Let's go see.

389
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,450
Did you write this couplet?

390
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,280
I haven't seen this couplet before.

391
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,320
The paper is already yellowing.

392
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,800
It should be quite old.

393
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:50,280
If this couplet was found in the secret compartment,

394
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:55,920
it means it has been in this desk all along.

395
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:58,680
This desk is old.

396
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,240
Oh, Miss.

397
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,960
You can't call it an old desk.

398
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:04,200
I found this at the market.

399
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,440
It is an antique piece of furniture.

400
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:07,520
You all know antique furniture

401
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:08,840
is very valuable, yeah.

402
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:10,080
Look at this wood grain,

403
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,080
and this color.

404
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,640
It's good stuff.

405
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:14,640
But we said earlier

406
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,160
that since Jueming is moving to a new home,

407
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:18,040
we should get him a new set of furniture.

408
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,440
I know, Miss.

409
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:20,880
But I asked the carpenter.

410
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,760
It takes at least ten days to make a set of tables.

411
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:23,400
There's not enough time.

412
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,960
Besides, for these secondhand finds,

413
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:29,080
using antique furniture shows more taste.

414
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:29,960
Right?

415
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,800
Yes.

416
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:33,520
I really like this table.

417
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,680
The older it is, the more character it has.

418
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,120
It has texture and taste.

419
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,520
Let's take a look.

420
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,560
This first line looks quite good.

421
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:48,040
The second line seems

422
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,360
a bit frivolous.

423
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:51,480
Flippant.

424
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,320
Would any of you like to complete it?

425
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:55,930
Match it with a couplet.

426
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,480
Give it a try.

427
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,560
I have one.

428
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:10,200
Green willows swaying in the wind,

429
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,880
weak branches and thin leaves,

430
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:17,920
dancing wildly in the spring.

431
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:19,840
How is it?

432
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:22,570
My literary talent is not bad, right, Dad?

433
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,200
I really didn't expect this.

434
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,120
Do you like it?

435
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,080
It's for you.

436
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,560
Okay, I'll take it.

437
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:31,500
Since Brother Su composed it,

438
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,530
I will definitely treasure it.

439
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,360
Alright,

440
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:39,280
then keep it safe.

441
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,080
Brother.

442
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,280
Brother, come up here!

443
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,360
Brother, come look!

444
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:59,040
Coming!

445
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,200
Brother.

446
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,600
What is it, brother? This...

447
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:11,720
Who wrote the second line of this couplet?

448
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:13,120
No one has been in your room.

449
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:14,800
Didn't you write it yourself?

450
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,000
Could it be that

451
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:21,200
someone is helping me in secret?

452
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,420
You treasure whatever he writes, don't you?

453
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:39,880
Let me do one.

454
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:41,080
Go ahead then.

455
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,680
Clouds hide the ancient temple.

456
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:49,680
Distant bells echo among the deep pines.

457
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,800
As expected of the young lady. This is great.

458
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:53,760
She is elegant and virtuous.

459
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:55,160
And has brilliant literary talent.

460
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,560
The mood and the poetry

461
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:57,880
match perfectly.

462
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:58,800
Then look at you.

463
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,640
What is this rubbish? What's wrong with me?

464
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:03,400
It's completely unpresentable.

465
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,810
You have no literary talent at all.

466
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,440
How could this...

467
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:18,680
I do not know which worthy sage

468
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,720
added this second line to my scroll.

469
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,440
Who matched this line,

470
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:24,420
and why give guidance so quietly?

471
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,680
How strange.

472
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,200
That's not right.

473
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:29,000
No, no.

474
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:30,560
After we put it in just now,

475
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:33,360
the four of us haven't touched this table!

476
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,800
Right, no one touched it.

477
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:38,640
This... this is haunted! Haunted!

478
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,480
Haunted?

479
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,280
How interesting.

480
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,120
Could this table have a spirit

481
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:48,400
that can automatically generate essays?

482
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,280
Interesting.

483
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,090
Let me write a few words.

484
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,040
Put the one you just put in

485
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:13,160
again to see.

486
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,720
Should we

487
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:26,280
take

488
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,960
another look?

489
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:29,930
It should be about time.

490
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,400
Let's take a look.

491
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,480
Come.

492
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:41,000
Why is it a blank piece of paper?

493
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:44,120
Am I seeing things?

494
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:46,280
There's nothing on it.

495
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:49,370
There really are words.

496
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:51,000
I am a poor scholar.

497
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:52,420
My name is Sun Wenhuai.

498
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:56,100
I live south of the Luo River. It's appearing! It's appearing!

499
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,600
The third house to the east.

500
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,760
I found your couplet brilliant.

501
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,280
I pondered hard for a matching line but failed.

502
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:06,040
So I ask who you are.

503
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:10,400
Why do these words look like they were just written?

504
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:14,520
Is this drawer really haunted?

505
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,000
There's an address here.

506
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:18,520
Let's go take a look.

507
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,000
If this person really exists,

508
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,280
I'd like to meet him.

509
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,680
That's right. You should go take a look. Go.

510
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,320
Who is it?

511
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,760
I am Jueming, a Buliangren.

512
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,600
Excuse me, is this Sun Wenhuai's house?

513
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,680
Sun Wenhuai? Hmm.

514
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:49,120
He... didn't he die a long time ago?

